Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as population protocols are a model of distributed computing and involve the use of finite automata. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses whether the rules of interactions between agents can be seen as a game from game theory. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as population protocols are a model of sensor networks. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is a possible category as the paper discusses the computation of predicates on initial configurations. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as population protocols involve the interaction of multiple agents.
